# Scope Control (MANDATORY)

## Only Do What the Ticket Asks

- Read the PRD section for the current ticket in `docs/product/FundRight-PRD.md` (e.g. FR-004) before writing any code
- Implement ONLY the deliverables and acceptance criteria listed for that ticket
- If the ticket says "modify component X", only modify component X
- If the ticket says "add schema for Y", only add the schema work specified

## Do NOT

- Refactor code that isn’t part of the current ticket
- Add docstrings, comments, or "cleanup" in files you didn’t need to change for the ticket
- Rename variables or components outside the ticket scope
- "Clean up" imports or formatting in unrelated files
- Add features, helpers, or dependencies not specified in the ticket
- Modify Vercel config, env, or tooling unless the ticket explicitly requires it
- Implement or depend on tickets that are not yet done (respect DEVLOG dependency order)

## When You Find Issues Outside Your Scope

- Do not fix bugs in other modules as a side effect
- Do not refactor code that "could be better" unless it’s in scope
- Note the issue in the commit message or for a follow-up ticket
- Let the project owner decide whether to create a new ticket

## File and Phase Boundaries

- Only touch files that are required to meet the ticket’s acceptance criteria
- Do not add Phase 2 or Phase 3 features (e.g. AI, full analytics dashboard) in Phase 1 tickets unless the ticket explicitly includes them
